## Example entry (✅ good — keep this style)

### INC-007 — Checkout p95 latency spike to 14s during Black Friday campaign
- **When:** 2024-11-29 13:42 UTC-3 to 14:18 UTC-3 (duration: 36 min)
- **Severity:** S1 — paid traffic could not complete purchase
- **Symptom:** Frontend `POST /checkout/complete` returned 504 Gateway Timeout for ~40% of requests; conversion dropped from 8.2% to 0.9%; Sentry breadcrumbs showed user retry-then-abandon pattern; Stripe webhook backlog grew to 12k events.
- **Affected:** ~3,800 checkout sessions; revenue impact ~R$ 142k (recovered ~85% via abandoned-cart email campaign over next 48h).
- **Root cause:** N+1 query in `OrderEventService.materializeCart()` introduced by PR #482 (refactor to "simplify" cart loading); each cart item triggered a separate `SELECT` against `product_variants`. Under normal load 8 items × 80ms = 640ms — acceptable. Under campaign load DB connection pool (size 20) saturated, queueing reached request timeout.
- **Trigger:** Marketing email campaign sent at 13:40 produced ~6x normal traffic over 5 minutes.
- **Fix (immediate):** Rolled back PR #482 at 14:11; recovery by 14:18.
- **Fix (durable):** [PR #498](url) reintroduced batched loading via `IN` query; added integration test asserting `cart_size <= 100 ⇒ db_queries <= 3` at [`test/integration/CartMaterializationTest.java:88`](test/integration/CartMaterializationTest.java#L88); added Datadog dashboard panel "checkout.db.queries_per_request" with alert at >10.
- **Prevention reflex:** Any PR touching `OrderEventService`, `CartService`, or `materializeCart()` MUST include a query-count assertion in tests. Code review checklist updated. The phrase "simplify cart loading" is a 🚩 — verify it doesn't unbatch.
- **Related:** ADR-012 (cart materialization strategy), BR-021 (checkout must complete in <2s p95), [[vendor-relationships]] Stripe entry (webhook backlog handling), [[anti-decisions]] AD-011 (in-memory cart cache experiment that increased complexity without solving root issue).
- **Captured:** 2024-08-20 by alice

